import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['date'] = pd.to_datetime(data['date'], format='%Y-%m-%d', errors='coerce')
    data = data[pd.notna(data['date'])]
    data = data.groupby('date').sum().reset_index()
    fig, ax = plt.subplots(figsize=(12, 6))
    sns.lineplot(x='date', y='wounds', data=data, ax=ax, label='Wounds')
    sns.lineplot(x='date', y='other', data=data, ax=ax, label='Other Injuries')
    sns.lineplot(x='date', y='disease', data=data, ax=ax, label='Diseases')
    plt.title('What is the overall trend of injuries and diseases during the Crimean War?', wrap=True)
    plt.xlabel('Date')
    plt.ylabel('Number of Injuries and Diseases')
    plt.legend()
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
```

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['wounds'] = pd.to_numeric(data['wounds'])
    sns.histplot(data=data, x='wounds', color='blue', kde=True)
    plt.axvline(data['wounds'].mean(), color='red', linestyle='dashed', linewidth=1, label='Mean')
    plt.axvline(data['wounds'].median(), color='green', linestyle='dashed', linewidth=1, label='Median')
    plt.legend()
    plt.title('What is the distribution of wounds during the Crimean War?')
    plt.xlabel('Number of wounds')
    plt.ylabel('Frequency')
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
```

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['date'] = pd.to_datetime(data['date'], format='%Y-%m-%d', errors='coerce')
    data = data[pd.notna(data['date'])]
    sns.set_style("darkgrid")
    chart = sns.lineplot(x='date', y='disease', data=data, color='red')
    chart.axhline(y=data['disease'].median(), color='blue', linestyle='--', label='Median')
    chart.legend(loc='upper left')
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    plt.title('What is the correlation between diseases and time during the Crimean War?', wrap=True)
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
```
